content.webTitle: FA Cup ties which could produce shock results

fields.headline: Ties to savour
fields.bodyText: Barnsley v Blackburn Barnsley's biggest hope lies in Blackburn's losing habit, six defeats in seven Premiership games. Rovers will look to Matt Jansen for goals. Shock potential: Fair Dagenham v Ipswich Even if the tie goes on, Ipswich are unlikely to be enamoured of the conditions, which should be good for Dagenham. Shock potential: Fair Leicester v Mansfield Stags will usually outrun foxes, or so Mansfield hope. Certainly Leicester's defence gives the Third Division side a chance. Shock potential: Good Liverpool v Birmingham The way Liverpool have been performing at home recently Birmingham could well take the holders back to St Andrews or even knock them out. Shock potential : Fair Norwich v Chelsea Chelsea will either win in style or struggle to survive. Maybe this is too obviously a surprise waiting to happen. Shock potential : Good Stoke v Everton It is tempting to say the real shock would be an Everton win. Certainly Stoke's home form suggests short shrift for Walter Smith's team. Shock potential: Good
